Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay near fine light red-brown; mixed inclusions. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Agelo(chos) From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0035.23 and British Museum 1925,0119.329 and 330 and 2011,5003.255 and 273. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0383)
